  "text": "In addition to the directionality information, one can also deduce the form of the coupling (i.e. the form of the dispersal functional) by examining the spread of the peaks. Following [CITATION_1] , the width of the curves can be quantified by the 'full width half-max' (width of the peak at half it's maximum value), denoted DT. Figure 3 shows the log-log plot of the DT values as a function of spatial separation Dx. For diffusive coupling, it has been observed [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] ) that the width of the peaks tends to grow as the distance squared from the target point. As shown in figure 3 the slope is approximately 0.5 suggesting that indeed the coupling is diffusive in nature.",
